Eight shops were engulfed by flames at a shopping centre in Mahikeng, North West, on Monday. Police spokesperson Brig Sabata Mokgwabone said the fire broke out in a Bradlows store about 6am. He said the fire had been contained. The cause was unknown. “There were also reports of looting, so we had to send our officers there,” said Mokgwabone, adding that no looting was reported to have occurred.